            <thetext>Testrunner&#39;s test application (AUT) currently only includes the application 
library. This is not enough for applications using further libraries or 
contribs in their code. It is very likely that application classes will depend 
on those other libraries when they are instantiated in unit tests. Therefore, 
the test application has to respect these additional libraries. This is best 
achieved through the &quot;libraries&quot; includer job.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
